data.title: High School
data.text:
After what Lufkin head football coach Todd Quick said has been a good summer for the Panthers, work begins Monday with after school practice as the team gears up for the regular season set to start later this month.

The Stephen F Austin Chapter of the Texas High School Basketball Officials Association is actively seeking dedicated and enthusiastic individuals to join our organization as basketball officials for the upcoming season.

With four outright district titles in the past five years, the Diboll Lumberjacks got a top 25 ranking in Class 3A Division I from Dave Campbell’s Texas Football magazine. However, despite those district titles, the Lumberjacks are not picked to win District 9-3A DI.

Huntington hosted a boys and girls basketball camp this week with each day having a different theme for the approximately 50 participants.

A pair of former Lufkin athletes are returning to their alma mater as members of the Lady Panthers’ and Panthers’ coaching staffs for the upcoming school year.

More than 50 campers got three days of skills work at the Lufkin Lady Panthers’ basketball camp this week at the Panther Activity Center.

Summer strength and conditioning and sport-specific skills workouts are ongoing for area high schools and Lufkin has been seeing well over 100 athletes show up on a daily basis.

One of the key performers on Lufkin’s playoff run to the third round of the baseball playoffs, Austin Lindsey, signed last week to play at the next level with Hill College.

Moving into a new district, thanks to winning an appeal with the UIL, alleviated a lot of travel concerns for the Lufkin Panthers for the upcoming football season.

With Lufkin in Class 5A Division I in football and no other schools in that classification and division within 70 miles, it’s not always easy for the Panthers to fill out the non-district schedule.

Lufkin got a pair of wins in the Texas Association of Basketball Coaches Boys Showcase last weekend and played two of its three games on the featured courts at the Southwest Athletic Center in Carrollton.

Earlier this week, the Legislative Council of the University Interscholastic League approved split divisions for the postseason for more sports including volleyball, basketball, soccer, softball and baseball, effective for the 2024-25 athletic year.

A seven-run third inning that saw 13 batters come to the plate propelled the Orange team to a 10-3 win over the Blue team in the 7th annual East Texas Senior All-Star Softball Game Thursday night at Lufkin High School.

Softball players from Lufkin, Diboll, Central and the surrounding area will play in the 7th annual East Texas Senior All-Star Softball Game at 7 p.m. Thursday at Lufkin High School.

Centerville Bulldogs sophomore guard Iain Kendrick was recognized by Texas Association of Basketball Coaches as the individual 3-point champion for Class A basketball in the state of Texas. Kendrick hit 122 3-pointers this season, the most in school history and the only Bulldog to ever bring…

Nacogdoches’ baseball team will have a new head coach in 2025 as former SFA baseball player Eric DeJesus was recently hired to lead the Dragons on the diamond.

On Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday evenings in late spring and early summer, the track at Hudson High School is full of activity. Kids from ages 6 to 18 show up each night for practice with the PTX track club, coached by Robert Smith, his wife Kate and a number of volunteers.

The unbreakable bond of Dunbar success continues to grow as four more alumni have earned spots in the Prairie View Interscholastic League Hall of Fame.

Hudson’ Lady Hornets finished second in District 18-4A and were awarded a pair of superlatives in the all-district softball voting along with four spots on the first team.

Two Diboll players received superlatives and four more were named to the District 21-3A baseball first team in voting done by the district’s coaches.

Hudson, under first-year head coach Tanner Hines, took first place in District 18-4A in the 2024 season, and the success of the team was recognized by the district coaches in the all-district selections.

For Hudson’s Cooper Weeks, a visit last summer to Southwestern College, an NAIA school in Winfield, Kansas, turned into a tryout for PhD Hoops in Dallas.

Diboll’s Alonquin Fisher was looking for the right fit to continue his track and field career at the collegiate level. Once he found the perfect one, he jumped on the opportunity.

Huntington’s postseason came to an end Friday afternoon as the Red Devils fell to the Franklin Lions 7-2 in the Class 3A Region III semifinals at Huntsville High School.

The Texas Association of Basketball Coaches announced the four finalists and winner of the Dean Weese Outstanding Coach Award recently, honoring coaches from around the state for their hard work and dedication to their student-athletes.

Lufkin senior pitcher/centerfielder Kaleb Hillis was named MVP of 16-5A in voting done by coaches in the district. Hillis’ performance on the mound and at the plate helped the Panthers go 13-2 in district play, clinching the top spot with a week left in the season.

In a pitcher’s duel between Huntington’s Alex Havard and Franklin’s Josh Atomanczyk, the Lions got just enough offense to come away with a 2-0 win in Game 1 of the best-of-three regional semifinal series at Huntsville High School Thursday night.

CeCe Rodgers and Benita Barlow have spent years working at their crafts with an eye on potentially taking their talents to the next level. On Monday, that hard work paid off as they held their signing ceremony in PCA’s Naranjo Auditorium.

The Huntington Red Devils are set for the fourth round after knocking off district rival Central Heights. Next up for Huntington is a best-of-three Class 3A Region III semifinal series against the Franklin Lions.

LONGVIEW — With Lufkin leading 3-0 going into the sixth inning, Forney fought back for two runs in the bottom of the sixth and battled for two more in the bottom of seventh to take a 4-3 walkoff win in the deciding Game 3 of the best-of-three regional quarterfinals over the Panthers here Sat…

HUDSON — Kyle Menard threw a four-hit shutout and the Orangefield Bobcats completed a two-game sweep with a 5-0 win over the Diboll Lumberjacks in Class 3A Region III quarterfinal action here Saturday afternoon.

Huntington fans were jammed up against the net behind home plate, begging their team for one more out.

BULLARD — It took three rounds into the playoffs before the Lufkin Panthers were faced with an elimination game. Once they did, they looked to Austin Lindsey to take the mound.

A week after climbing out of a 1-0 hole, the Diboll Lumberjacks will need a repeat in the regional quarterfinals. After waiting out a pair of delays, the Orangefield Bobcats got the better of the Lumberjacks, taking a 6-2 win in the opener of a best-of-three series at Lamar University in Bea…

Solid pitching and defense have been constants for the Diboll Lumberjacks this season, and if the last two games are any indication, the bats are going to cause opponents some problems.

Coming off a 6-20 season in 2023, a run into the third round of the Class 3A playoffs would not have seemed likely. But that’s where the Huntington Red Devils have advanced.

BULLARD — Forney got its leadoff batter on base in each of the first five innings and the Jackrabbits were able to push across four runs off Lufkin starter Kaleb Hillis. Those four runs were enough to give Forney a 4-1 win over the Panthers in Game 1 of the best-of-three regional quarterfina…

When looking for a key to Lufkin’s success this season, it’s not any particular moment in a game, even though a comeback against Huntsville in the District 16-5A opener stands out.

QB Javion Johnson threw a pair of touchdown passes, one to KeVondrick Taylor and one to Krisean Preston, to highlight the scoring by Lufkin’s first team in Tuesday’s annual spring game at John Outlaw Field at Abe Martin Stadium.

With the recent move to the Big 12, the University of Houston athletic programs are now competing at the highest level of competition, including a basketball team that spent time as the No. 1 team in the nation.
